<Content>Okay, Expected More If you in town for an event at the convention center, the property is right next door, which is convenient. If you are in town as a tourist (or combo) stay somewhere else. It's too far walk to the features and attractions of Boston. The hotel itself is not very special for the price (even by Boston standards). Normal or bland are words I would use to describe everything from food to cleanliness to room features, etc. Decor seems dated, and I didn't find the heavenly bed as anything special. Sound proofing is not up to standards - I could hear the TV next door. I'd expect this in a less property, but not a Westin. Not much is within walking distance. The tea party boat is closed until 2009. You could visit Harpoon Brewery. For restaurants try Barking Crab, Anthony's Pier 4, or No Name Restuarant (all within walking distance). I might stay here again if going to the convention center (or try the Renaissance 2 blocks away), otherwise I'd stay somewhere else. Nothing special. Also - the Boston taxes of hotel tax, city tax, and tourism tax really add up. 
