<Author>jesann
<Content>Good hotel - Happy to stay again We picked this hotel following much research for our four-day break in Boston. The hotel gave us the amenities we wanted (pool /health club) at a competitive price for Boston.  We were certainly not disappointed as this hotel was well up to our expectations. We had a nice king-size room on the 13th floor with a great view of the Boston skyline (ask for a room overlooking Boston). The hotel is situated in South Boston. This is a short way from the down town area which is a good walk. The hotel is in a business area which is a little off the tourist path and there are very few places to eat in the immediate area. The Westin is certainly not a 'waterfront hotel' though you could see the water from the 13th floor. It is several blocks back from the waterfront, which in itself has yet to be further developed.We choose to use public transportation for our stay including the trip from and back to Logan Airport. The MTBA provides an excellent service to the nearby T station at the world trade centre / convention centre stop. As you leave the T station the Westin is directly in front of you and it is no more than a 5 minute walk. A $15 Charlie card gives you 7 day unlimited use of the transportation network which is quick and efficient, covering virtually the whole of Boston and Logan. (The Silver line connects the Airport to South Boston. It use system of over / underground trolley buses. The Silverline also goes on to connect with the rest of the network at South station) The hotel itself was friendly with a large open unfussy lobby.Check in was quick and with a smile. The room met our requirements though it was not spotless. Likewise the pool and spa were welcoming after a long tiring day but a little grubby around the edges. There were a lot of children using the facilities during our stay and the pool was often overloaded. The changing rooms were clean but a little small for busy periods.The room was quite during the week nights but Saturday night things got to say the least rowdy. Doors were crashing and there was much shouting / screaming - must have been a good party!We did not eat in the restaurant (buffet breakfast = $22pp) Overall a good hotel for visitors especially if you're happy to spend the day out exploring beautiful historic Boston. (We left early in the mornings and didn't get back until late evening.) We had a fabulous trip and a good hotel experience. I would recommend this Westin based on the current rates and quality of service. 
