<Content>Good, not great. We arrived in Boston 2 days ago for a weekend trip with friends. I have always enjoyed staying in Westin's due to the consistency of service, style and amenities in each location. For the most part this location lives up to the Westin experience.The hotel is location in South Boston near the waterfront. Personally I would not be going to Boston for the waterfront versus the entire city itself. It is about .7 miles from the T and Amtrack South Station. From there you can continue NW to the financial district, and just a little bit further is The Boston Common. A little walking or a short cab ride to the heart of Boston. You also have access to the Red Line T direct to Harvaed and Cambridge from the above station. Some may like the location versus downtown because of the crowds. On our last visit we stayed at the Nine Zero and loved but you have to like being right in the city.The lobby is great with many couches, chairs and nookes. Reception was fast and curteous. Rooms are big, comfortable with a large flat screen. There is a Starbucks near the lobby and a restaurant (we did not use). We ate at Good Life (great burger and outstanding fries) in the financial district and Grill 23 (Expensive but worth it if you like good steak without going to a Mortons chain. Similar to the The Metropolitan in Seattle).My two concerns where personel related. One, the concierge was worthless and plainly uninterested in my business. I asked for food reccomedations and was told walk up Summer until it ends and there are some restaurants. Well, Summer never ends and no suggestions or questions were asked as to preferences. No list or even a single wiff of interest in whether I was satisfied. Second, the maid service was up at 8 am talking extremley loud in the hallway. While I asked them politley to keep the noise down I really do not feel it is necessary for me to leave the room to wuiet the staff. Also, whoever designed the floors decided to place the maids closet/workroom near the corner of many of the rooms on the floor. The maid service also decided to place their large white carts in the hallway across from our room and others at midnight. Its takes a little of the glamour off the location to walk into those carts after a nice dinner downtown.Those concerns aside, I do reccomend this location and hope (I will call the GM) they improve the little things in the future 
