<Content>Perfect for business traveler attending the conference next door I stayed here from April 15-18 for the AIIM conference. I was here for a conference and for that, location is perfect. The hotel has a skywalk way on the mezzanine level to the new conference center. You can stay indoors the entire time which is great when weather in Boston is crappy which I experienced. There was a lot of wind and rainstorms during my stay in Boston so weather was not conducive to walking around. My husband and daughter (4 years old) came w/ me on this business trip. So things we liked:1) Nice ambience -- very modern decor. 2) Nice lounge area where you can sit around for snacks  drinks. Good alternative to eating at the only restaurant at the hotel, Sauciety.3) Indoor Pool -- for my daughter who loves to swim 4) Proximity to the Conference  airport-- as I was attending a conference there.Things we did not like:1) Location is a bummer if you are a leisure traveler trying to experience Boston -- This is not really Boston, it's South Boston, parts of which are still really rough neighborhood. Not a good place to walk around even if weather cooperated. Kind of a bummer for my family that was there for leisure.2) Very few restaurants around -- so you are sort of tied to the one restaurant on the premise. We did go and try the Legal Test Kitchen (5 min cab ride and probably within walking distance) -- which was fabulous. But food is a little expensive if you have to eat all your meals at the hotel3) Service is not quite there. First night we were on the top floor and there was this little loud noise from a fan they have up on the top of the building w/o enough insulation. Really loud and there was something wrong w/ the temperature control in the room and it was so hot. Next morning, I changed to a couple floors down and I didn't have the noise or temperature issues. On a separate occasion, my husband took my 4 year old for lunch at the hotel restaurant. Asked for ketchup and never got it for my daughter after asking 3-4 times to the waiter. He would have helped himself if he could find the ketchup.Last year in June, I stayed at the Hyatt Cambridge for a conference. This hotel is nicer, newer, more amenities and definitely more convenient location to the conference center. But one of these days, I would love to stay at one of those hotels in Copley Square to get the full Boston experience. For price comparisons, I got a conference rate of $229 per night. I hope they work out the kinks in the service -- it would be so much better then. 
