<Content>Brand New Hotel and still having some operational difficulties at times.. My family and I stayed here due to a great introductory rate of $149. For this rate we got a room on the 4th floor with a view of the rooftop air conditioning system and not much else, but it wasn't a problem. The floor itself is quiet and we heard no noise from the outside except an occasional airplane in the distance. We have stayed in Boston many times and knew that this hotel is not close to the touristy areas, but public transportation is closeby. The beds were comfortable, the large flatscreen TV and other decor was modern, and the bathroom size was more than adequate.The main issues we had with the hotel were things that made the hotel seem cheap - such as there being absolutely no super hot  water in either the shower in our room or the ladies'/men's locker room, no matter what time we took our showers. Also, the fact that the soap dispenser in the locker room was the plastic kind that stick to the wall, and in fact had been broken off of the wall. It would have been nice if the hotel had large pump-style containers of shampoo and conditioner in the shower as well as the varous toiletries available in case you forgot your own (or the dispenser was torn from the wall). I've been in other hotels that supply this for their guests and it is much appreciated. Also, as other people have noted, this hotel does nickel and dime their guests with the expensive room service charges, internet charges, and very expensive parking.There is a pool and a large workout room which our family used. The pool ranges from 3 feet to 4.5 feet deep, and is well heated. There is also a hot tub in the pool area.We didn't eat in the restaurant but we did order room service. We placed a small order fairly late (around 9:30 or 10 PM) and it took over 45 minutes to come to the room.As other guests have noted, there are few options for dining closeby. Upon checkout, we discovered that the computer system was down and they were manually checking people out of their rooms. We called several hours later after we arrived home to confirm that our checkout was completed properly, and learned that the computers were still down. We had to wonder how they managed to check the guests into the hotel that day.All in all, the place is still working out the kinks. It's a perfectly good place to stay if you are going to an event at the convention center, or if you get a good rate and don't mind using the public transporation to get around. 
